EasyOverrider

Interface ParamDescription<O,P>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of object in question
    P - the type of the parameter in question
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ParamDescriptionBase, ParamDescriptionCollection, ParamDescriptionMap, ParamDescriptionSingle

    public interface ParamDescription<O,P>
    This represents a parameter in an object and how to get and set it.
    There are five pieces used to describe a parameter.
    • Class parentClass - This is the class that the parameter exists in.
    • Class paramClass - This is the raw class of the parameter.
    • String name - This is the name of the parameter (usually the variable name).
    • Function getter - This is a reference to the getter for the parameter.
    • ParamMethodRestriction paramMethodRestriction - This is used to describe what method calls this parameter should be included in.
